# Release Workflow — Update Product Page with New Exe

Whenever a new Electron exe is built (via `npm run build` or electron-builder), the latest installer must be copied to the `site/` folder so the Netlify product page serves the current release.

## Steps after every new build

1. Compress the new exe into a zip using 7-Zip (max compression) and place it in `site/`:
   ```powershell
   & "C:\Program Files\7-Zip\7z.exe" a -tzip -mx=9 "site\Vibe-Blocking-IDE-Setup.zip" "dist-electron\Vibe Blocking IDE Setup X.X.X.exe"
   ```
2. The `site/script.js` download link already points to `Vibe-Blocking-IDE-Setup.zip` — no code change needed.
3. Remind the user to re-upload the `site/` folder to Netlify (or redeploy) to publish the update.

## File layout

```
site/
  index.html
  style.css
  script.js
  paypal-qr.png
  Vibe-Blocking-IDE-Setup.zip   ← always the latest build (compressed)
  netlify.toml
```
